	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64277986"><p>All our probes have been launched inline with the orbital plane to take advantage of planetary gravity assists to get them out of Sol's gravity well. If you're communicating with your probes, you're going to be broadcasting along the same plane, which increases the odds of emissions in our direction. If those probes are on the far side of that solar system, they will also be broadcasting in our direction, albeit at a bee's fart of a power level. Mal-2 has already highlighted the possibility of interplanetar<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

